Sphinx Documentation
--------------------

Note: Sphinx actually runs and imports python code, so broken code, or code not in conf.py sys.path, cannot be documented!

1.  Get Sphinx [http://sphinx.pocoo.org/]
    [python setup.py build/install]

2.  (Optional, do this step if you activate numpy extension in conf.py) 
    Install numpydoc [http://pypi.python.org/pypi/numpydoc] 

3.  In Makefile point to your own copy of sphinx-build, e.g.
    [SPHINXBUILD   = /Users/yourname/CODES/Sphinx-1.0.6/sphinx-build.py]

4.  From within doc/ directory 
    >> touch *.rst
    >> make html  [or make latex]

5.  Navigate to doc/_build/html and open index.html to view and browse the documentation
